oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Home of J. J. Thompson
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the house bought by J. J. Thompson in the late 1860s. The family is posed in front of the brick home's porch. The woman standing on the far left with the bird cage was the family tutor. The house was originally built in the 1830s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Families; Birdcages
